Wash and dry produce.

Halve, peel, and dice @onion{1} into 1⁄2-inch pieces. Core, deseed, and
dice @green bell pepper{1} into 1⁄2-inch pieces. Peel and mince @garlic{1%clove}.
Finely chop @cilantro{1/4%ounce}.

Place @jasmine rice{3/4%cup} in a #fine-mesh strainer{}; rinse under cold water
until water runs clear. Set aside until ready to use.

> No fine-mesh strainer? No problem! Rinse rice in a medium bowl and drain
> water using your hand to block the rice from escaping!

Open package of @diced skinless dark meat chicken{10%ounce} and drain off any
excess liquid.

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat.
Add chicken, onion, and bell pepper in a single layer; season with
@sazón seasoning{1%unit} and @salt{1/4%tsp}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until
veggies are browned and chicken is cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

> Use 2 TBSP Loisa Organic Sazón Seasoning and 1⁄2 tsp salt for 4 servings.

Stir in garlic and @tomato paste{1%unit}; cook, stirring, until garlic is
fragrant and tomato paste darkens, ~{1-2%minutes}.

To pan with chicken and veggies, add rice, @chicken stock concentrate{2%units},
@sazón seasoning{2%tsp}, @salt{1/2%tsp}, and @water{1 1/4%cups}+2 TBSP; stir to
combine.

> Use 4 tsp Loisa Organic Sazón Seasoning, 1 tsp salt, and 2 1⁄2 cups water for 4
> servings.

Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is
tender, ~{20%minutes}. Remove from heat.

Fluff rice with a #fork{} and stir in half the cilantro. Cover and let stand
until excess liquid has absorbed, ~{8-10%minutes} more.

Divide chicken and rice between shallow #bowls{} and garnish with remaining
cilantro. Serve.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.